TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Extract records for timestamp>'$$LOAD_LAST_TS'. Initial value of incremental load parameter '$$LOAD_LAST_TS' is '01/01/1111 00:00:00' and is get updated with CREATE_TS value.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: SQ_TSNAP

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT DISTINCT TS.SNAP_ID, TC.CORP_CD, TS.PERIOD_ID, TS.MODEL_TYP_CD, TS.RUN_MODE_CD, TS.SNAP_SEQ_NB, TS.CREATE_TS, TS.SNAP_APC_TYP_CD, TS.SNAP_XMIT_STAT_CD, TS.SNAP_FREQ_CD, TS.SNAP_RUN_STAT_CD, TS.CREATE_USER_ID, C.CORP_ABBR_NM, SMC.CD_NM CD_NM_MODEL, SFC.CD_NM CD_NM_FREQUENCY, TS.REQ_RUN_TM_UPDT_TS FROM VRAP.TSNAP TS INNER JOIN (SELECT TH.SNAP_ID,MAX(HIST_INSRT_TS) HIST_INSRT_TS FROM VRAP.TSNAP_HIST TH GROUP BY TH.SNAP_ID ) TSH ON TS.SNAP_ID=TSH.SNAP_ID INNER JOIN VRAP.TVNDR_REBT_CD SFC ON TS.SNAP_FREQ_CD=SFC.CD_NB AND SFC.TYP_CD=157 INNER JOIN VRAP.TVNDR_REBT_CD SMC ON TS.MODEL_TYP_CD=SMC.CD_NMON_TXT AND SMC.TYP_CD=139 INNER JOIN VRAP.TCORP C ON C.CORP_CD=TS.CORP_CD INNER JOIN VRAP.TCORP_MODEL_TYP_CD TC ON TC.MODEL_TYP_CD =TS.MODEL_TYP_CD WHERE TSH.HIST_INSRT_TS>TIMESTAMP('$$LOAD_LAST_TS') WITH UR
